properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 15 at 3:09PM PST until January 16 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Storm Warning, south winds 40 to 50 kt and seas
17 to 20 feet at 10 seconds. For the Gale Warning, southwest
winds 30 to 40 kt and seas 20 feet at 10 to 13 seconds.

* WHERE...Coastal Waters From Cape Flattery To James Island Out
10 Nm, Coastal Waters From James Island To Point Grenville Out
10 Nm, Coastal Waters From Point Grenville To Cape Shoalwater
Out 10 Nm, Coastal Waters From Cape Flattery To James Island
10 To 60 Nm, Coastal Waters From James Island To Point
Grenville 10 To 60 Nm and Coastal Waters From Point Grenville
To Cape Shoalwater 10 To 60 Nm.

* WHEN...For the Storm Warning, until 10 PM PST this evening.
For the Gale Warning, from 10 PM this evening to 4 AM PST
Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Very strong winds will cause hazardous seas which
could capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should remain in port, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 PM PST THIS EVENING... ...GALE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 10 PM THIS EVENING TO 4 AM PST THURSDAY
